<br>
I'll post numbers when I'm less tired, but I've determined that you save (specialize skill / ~17.5) percent of the casting cost.  Every time.  I tried this with 200 sp.evo, 50 abj, and 50 alt, and it was consistent.<br>
<br>
Where the ~17.5 comes from, I'm not sure.  It's actually probably ~1750 since nn% of X is actually calculated as 0.nn * X.  ~1750 is probably some calc of my level and my int or something.  For instance, my int was 220 so maybe it's really 8*220=1760.  I really don't know.  I just know at level 57 with 220 int and no buffs and no SCM, I got ~(200 / 17.5)% reduction.  It did not seem to be affected by actual spell skill, as I got exactly the same results at 235 (alt) as 208 (conj).<br>
