Good job.<br>
<br>
If I am reading your data correctly than it appears that my original guess is right. Spell Casting Mastery is actually better than Mental Clarity.<br>
<br>
I am not the best with mathematics, but if a caster has 3000 mana and you tack on 14.8% than you are effectively adding 444 mana. With FT3, it takes around 15~16min to recover 444 mana.<br>
<br>
On a raid, you are no doubt going to exhaust all your mana so you would reap all the benefits of SCM3 ...and might not have the time to take advantage of MC3. And no doubt, if you are raiding, you are probably going to be good on mana regen as is.<br>
<br>
<br>
In XP grind the decision becomes harder but might lean toward MC3 since most likely you will rarely be full mana.<br>
<br>
Definately something to think about... <p><p align="center">
